Vulcan: {
	DisplayName: Vulcan
	Start: So, you're the one who defeated that naughty candle, I see. How delightful! I'm Vulcan, the blacksmith, so if you need to reforge your armour, speak to me!
	Cup: Oh, smokes... How did you... Wherever you found this, put it back! It's nothing but trouble!
	PoorUnfortunateSoul: Hey! I definitely remember those! They are usually channelled with some item and serve as, well... a live hard drive! They divide your brain into fractions and allow you to store only the most important things in your memory, taking away useless stuff. The aristocrats took them to meetings to retain boring information while sleeping. But, don't worry, they're harmless! ...it just depends on the owner.
	Nickname: Same name, huh? Easier to remember.

	Buttons: {
		Reforge: Reforge
		Lore: Lore
	}

	Chat: {
		1: Hello there! Hope nobody was following you. Need anything reforged?
		2: Oh, don't make a sad face. Just ignore all of your problems, they are far away, and you are here. Look at me, I'm completely calm. They're never gonna find us. Right?
		3: Don't worry, it's okay to be hated. Only those who are worse think bad things about us. Those who are better than us... they just don't care!
		4: No-no-no, I'd rather stay here. Not in the mood to turn into a huge monstrous skull today.
		5: I'm not as good a blacksmith as I used to be. All because of that damned candle... I hope she learns her lesson.
		6: If you need to reforge your armor, speak to me!
		7: Have you noticed that some characters are significantly smaller or larger than others? No, this is not due to lack of style and bad taste, mostly. It's just sand people are born huge and shapeless, and their bodies compress with age, filling up with experience and trauma. So yes, those who want to lose weight may prefer to watch some snotty melodramas instead of a healthy diet and gym. Unbelievable!
	}

	LoreStart: Oh, hello again! So... it looks like you put an end to her mischiefs, and the vessel won't cause any more trouble? In that case, I can finally tell you my story. It's sad, so get your napkins ready.

	Lore: {
		0: You know, I wasn't always this desperate. I had a joyful, carefree life, but one day everything has gone to the dogs. I had to hide from the Nexus people in some boring caves deep underground. No matter how many weapons I forged and how many things I built, there was no one around to evaluate my work! And then I got a terrible idea.
		1: I picked up wax and ashes and made a sculpture, linked it to this place so it couldn't escape and be found by someone outside, and brought it to life using my cup with living flame. Seemed like a great plan, the perfect friend who wouldn't betray you and would support any of your ventures...
		2: Of course, if you've read enough books and watched enough movies, you know what's wrong with a story like this. She turned out to be too intrusive, too coarse and rough and irritating and was getting everywhere! And since I linked her to the underworld, I'd be stuck with her forever!
		3: I couldn't take her life without her will, but I needed to keep her away... Then I came up with another brilliant idea, I collected bones and stones and made another living sculpture. It seemed to me that the only way to get rid of that candle was to shift her focus, so I made him strong, hot, and came up with a crazy epic lore to get her attention.
		4: When I thought I was finally alone, he came to me, exhausted and depressed: apparently, even with his patience, he couldn't stand her shenanigans. I was about to make another statue to cure his depression, but then realized that I'd already spent all the flame on those two.
		5: Later that night, he broke into my floor, ripped his flame out of his chest in the most dramatic way possible, put it back in the cup and tied it with chains into a knot, leaving only a pile of stones behind. I'd never seen my candle in such a rage, she couldn't believe that her beloved just disappeared, and blamed me for his imprisonment.
		6: She ruined my ruins, took the cup along with a huge cage and a set of keys, and went deep underground... I don't know what she was trying to do, maybe fake her escape to ingratiate herself with some stranger... Well, if you wanna hear this story again, just ask, I have nothing much to do anyway.
	}

	TownNPCMood: {
		Content: I am content.
		NoHome: I hate not having a home.
		FarFromHome: I am too far from home.
